\f0\b\fs52 \cf0 Cider Brined Grilled Stuffed Pork Chops\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl240\ql\qnatural

\f1\fs32 \cf2 Serves:  
\b0 \cf0 3 servings\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Ingredients\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}3 bone-in, or boneless pork chops, about 2 pounds total\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Brine:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}4 cups apple cider\
{\listtext	\'95	}2 cups oatmeal {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/stout/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 stout}} or other dark beer\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup kosher salt\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/raw-sugar/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 raw sugar}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon chipotle chili powder\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Cider Reduction:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 cups {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/apple-cider/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 apple cider}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Apple {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/stuffing/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Stuffing}}:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls4\ilvl0
\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1 1/2 apples ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pink-lady/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Pink Lady}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/honey/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Honey}} Crisps, or Cameo) cored and sliced 1/4-inch thick, grilled, about 1 minute each side, and diced\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/mesquite/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 mesquite}} honey\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon chipotle {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/chili-powder/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 chili powder}}\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon ground {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/cinnamon/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 cinnamon}}\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\f0\b\fs44 \cf0 Directions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural

\f1\b0\fs42 \cf0 Red Chili Caramelized Pecans, recipe follows\
For the brine:\
Combine all ingredients in a large container with a tight fitting lid.\
Take the pork chops and insert a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/fillet/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 fillet}} knife into the side of each pork chop. Create a 2-inch slice along the side moving your knife along the inside of the chop creating a pocket. Be careful not to pierce the outer sides of the chop. Place the pork chops in the brine for anywhere from 1 hour or up to 24 hours in the refrigerator.\
For the reduction:\
Add the cider to a medium {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/saucepan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 saucepan}} over medium heat. Cook the cider, skimming off any scum that comes to the surface, until is becomes syrupy and is reduced to about 1/4 cup.\
For the stuffing:\
Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.\
Preheat grill to high.\
Remove the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pork/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 pork chops}} from the brine, rinse and pat dry with paper towels. Stuff the cavity with the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/apple/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 apples}} and grill for about 10 minutes on each side. Remove from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/grill/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 grill}} to a serving platter and let rest for about 10 minutes. Brush with the cider {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/reduction/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 reduction}}, sprinkle with the chopped caramelized pecans and enjoy!\
Red Chili Caramelized {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/pecan/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 Pecans}}:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl400\ql\qnatural
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1/2 pound white cane sugar\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/4 cup water\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 pound whole pecans\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 tablespoon vanilla extract\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 teaspoon red chili powder\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl400\sa140\ql\qnatural
\cf0 In a heavy-bottomed pot, cook the sugar and water until the temperature reaches 275 degrees F on a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/candyfat-thermometer/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 candy thermometer}}. Add the pecans and stir to coat with the sugar. Once the sugar begins to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/caramelize/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 caramelize}} add the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/extracts/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 vanilla extract}} and stir gently but constantly until fully caramelized. Pour onto a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/silpat/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf2 silpat}} lined baking sheet to let cool, then sprinkle with the red chili powder.\
* Cook's Note: Working with cooked sugar is dangerous and should be approached with extreme caution.\
